 great
hurry, and said to the King, "The flowers are
poisonous; we must go on to the other side."

"How do you know that?" said the King.
"Because I tasted one of them," said Alice.
"I beg your pardon," said the King, "but if
you've been tasting them, you must know as
well as I do." "I don't know," said Alice. "I
taste things without knowing whether they're
sweet or sour." "You taste them from the
seeds," said the Queen, "and you know it's not
from the seeds that poison is got." "I never saw
the seeds," said Alice. "There are no seeds in
the middle of a flower," said the Queen. "If you
taste from the outside of a flower, you'd get no
poison." "Why, there's poison in this one,"
